        end_time_formatted: "2026-03-01 23:59",
        detail: "Behind every powerful woman… are more powerful women.\nDirect from Broadway comes the acclaimed Tony Award®-winning musical SUFFS, about the brilliant, passionate, and funny American women who fought tirelessly for the right to vote.\n\n\n\n“A production that is just as powerful and relevant as its Broadway debut.” — BroadwayWorld San Francisco\n\n\n“Not since Hamilton has a show been as invigorating and spirited as the Tony Award-winning musical SUFFS.” — TheatreMania\n\nCreated by Shaina Taub, this “thrilling, inspiring and dazzlingly entertaining” (Variety) new musical boldly explores the triumphs and failures of a struggle for equality that’s far from over. Winner of the Outer Critics Circle Award for Best New Musical.\n\n\nCALL TIME EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW: Discover the poignant family connection that links SUFFS to the Palmetto State. Cast member Victoria Pekel (image right), discovered that her own great-grandmother, a South Carolina native, lived a legacy strikingly similar to the woman she now portrays on stage.\nRead now\n\n\n\n\nListen to the album and see why SUFFS won the Tony Award for Best Score.",
